# AI-Controlled Component Features

Our system provides comprehensive AI control over component styling and behavior through various control sets. Below is a detailed breakdown of all available features.

## 1. Background Controls
Control component background appearance:
- Background color (any valid CSS color)
- Background image (URL or data URL)
- Background image removal
- Transparency/opacity
- Combined color and image effects

## 2. Border Controls
Manage component borders and shadows:
- Border width (all sides or individual)
- Border style (solid, dashed, dotted, etc.)
- Border color
- Border radius (all corners or individual)
- Inner shadows
- Outer shadows
- Border presets

## 3. Spacing Controls
Handle component spacing:
- Padding (all sides or individual)
- Margin (all sides or individual)
- Gap between flex items
- Spacing presets:
  - Small (8px)
  - Medium (16px)
  - Large (24px)
- Auto margins for centering

## 4. Size Controls
Manage component dimensions:
- Width and height
- Minimum/maximum constraints
- Aspect ratio
- Fit content options
- Size presets:
  - Square (equal width/height)
  - Banner (full width, fixed height)
  - Card (fixed width, auto height)
  - Full (100% width/height)
- Responsive sizing (%, vw, vh)
- Calc expressions support

## 5. Layout Controls
Control flex container behavior:
- Display type (flex, block, etc.)
- Flex direction (row, column)
- Flex wrap
- Justify content
- Align items
- Align content
- Child element properties:
  - Flex grow/shrink
  - Flex basis
  - Order
- Layout presets:
  - Row layout
  - Column layout
  - Grid-like layout
  - Centered layout
  - Space between

